Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Vantage is a recently completed and architecturally designed development encompassing 120 apartments, ground floor commercial and a fully landscaped outdoor area with swimming pool and BBQ area. The development is ideally located in the heart of Bruce, close to Canberra Stadium, University of Canberra, Canberra Institute of Technology, Australian Institute of Sport, Calvary Hospital and Fern Hill Business Park. Units 122 and 123 are combined to provide 194sqm of high grade ground floor commercial accommodation with fantastic street exposure and can be used for a variety of uses including medical, shop and restaurant. The units are ready to be fitted out to the incoming occupier's desired sceficication and can be seperated into smaller units of 66sqm and 128sqm if required. The units also include 8 car parks of which 6 are on-grade directly behind the units and 2 in the secure basement.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: Brand New Ground Floor Commercial Unit in the Heart of Bruce!

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Bruce is located approximately half way between Belconnen and Canberra CBD.

Proximity is a high density residential development which has been recently completed by Village Building Company. The development is located on the corner of Battye Street and Braybrooke Street, in close 'proximity' to:
- Australian Institute of Sport (AIS)
- Canberra Stadium
- University of Canberra (UC)
- Canberra Institute of Technology (CIT)
- Calvary Hospital
- Canberra International Sports and Aquatic Centre (CISAC)


Unit 57 is located on the ground floor measuring 67sqm and can be utilised as a commercial or residential unit.
The unit title also comprises the following subsidiaries on Units Plan 3151:
Subsidiary (1) Front courtyard facing onto the common car park (23sqm)
Subsidiary (2) Basement car park (13sqm)
Subsidiary (3) Storage (3sqm)

The adjacent ground floor units are fully occupied and comprise a hairdresser, restaurant, beauty lounge and custom design homes.

The unit is currently leased to Dexterity Health expiring 6 July 2012 with the current rental being $2,015/month ($360/sqm pa) payable monthly in advance.

The unit would therefore suit an investor or owner occupier looking to move in next year.

For further information please call Duane Dawson or Mark Nicholls of CBRE.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: Rare opportunity to purchase a boutique unit in Bruce!

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: LEASED TO BLUE CHIP TENANT UNTIL JULY 18

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
15 Thynne Street is located within the quiet leafy suburb of Bruce, approximately 2kms from Belconnen Town Centre and approximately 7kms from Canberra City Centre. Bruce is well known for its pleasant bush setting, offering an excellent living and working environment. The area houses a mix of commercial, leisure, medical and educational facilities, plus a range of residential accommodation from single title dwellings to medium and higher density townhouse and apartment complexes.

Notable landmarks within the area include:

• University of Canberra
• Calvary Hospital
• Australian Institute of Sport
• Canberra Stadium
• Canberra International Sports and Aquatic Centre
• Canberra Institute of Technology

15 Thynne Street, known as The Don Gray Building, is a single title two storey office building of 2,400sqm*. The building sits on a 4,800sqm* site with a bitumen sealed car accommodating 52* spaces. The property is currently 100% occupied by Telstra Corporation Limited expiring 31 July 2018 with a passing NET income of $695,881* pa ($57,990/month)*.

Zoned within the Territory Plan as CZ5 (Mixed Use) permitting uses such as 'residential' and 'community', the site offers plenty of redevelopment potential (subject to Crown Lease Variation) and potential to combine with the property in front.

The property is offered for sale by Expression of Interest Closing Thursday 13th July 2017.

*Approx
